1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,680
As for me, there’s a saying: they asked the nail, “Why did you go into the wall?”

2
00:00:02,720 --> 00:00:06,360
He answered, “From how much they hit my head”

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:11,880
I didn’t sell cigarettes by choice, but I was an employee

4
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:15,839
My salary was 12,000 Syrian Lira, working in the Water Authority

5
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:21,960
After I started working, Air Force Intelligence raided my house and detained my brother, taking him to Sednaya Prison

6
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:28,320
When they raided my place and I fled, I had 10 children

7
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:31,480
They needed food and bread

8
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:36,479
I bought a taxi without papers and drove it, but the income wasn’t enough

9
00:00:36,799 --> 00:00:40,399
And cigarette trade wasn’t punishable by execution or anything like that

10
00:00:40,439 --> 00:00:45,880
But the organization imposed execution on us, even though it wasn’t for cigarette trade

11
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:48,000
Their judgments became vindictive

12
00:00:48,159 --> 00:00:53,640
They invented charges,collaboration, cigarettes, ammunition,just to sentence us to execution

13
00:00:53,719 --> 00:00:59,200
I was forced into cigarette trade. I have children and pay rent for two houses

14
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:04,640
Every day I’d buy bread for 2,000 or 3,000 Syrian Lira, and there was no other work

15
00:01:04,799 --> 00:01:08,280
With the organization, either you join them or remain jobless

16
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:10,599
So how could I feed my children?

17
00:01:10,799 --> 00:01:15,359
Should I trade cigarettes to earn a living and feed them, or let them starve to death?

18
00:01:15,879 --> 00:01:21,799
Just like many others, there were about 2,000 people

19
00:01:21,959 --> 00:01:24,000
And I was under a death sentence
